The '''KT90''' is a [[vacuum tube]] used in audio applications. Typically, it is used in hi-fi or electric [[guitar amplifier]] applications. KT90 was developed by [[Elektronska Industrija Niš]] (Ei).

== Features ==
The KT90, or in full, "Kinkless Tetrode 90", is a [[Beam tetrode|beam power tetrode]] and features the same octal socket as its smaller variant, the [[KT88]]. It may therefore be used as a substitute, given appropriate re-biasing when used in push-pull configuration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.duncanamps.com/tdsl/show.php?des=KT90 |title=TDSL Tube data [KT90&#93; |publisher=Duncanamps.com |date=2010-02-28 |accessdate=2011-09-08}}</ref>

The KT90 is currently manufactured by [[Electro-Harmonix]], who claim that, despite its different construction, it possesses similar sound characteristics to the [[EL34]] valve.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ehx.com/products/kt90 |title=KT90 – Power Vacuum Tube|publisher=Electro-Harmonix |date= |accessdate=2012-07-25}}</ref> Semi-formal research has been conducted by U.K. supplier Watford Valves who have published a test report.<ref>http://www.watfordvalves.com/cgi-bin/documents/testreport_42.pdf</ref> (This research is described here as "semi-formal" because it consists primarily of listening evaluations which may be subjective, rather than electrical analyses of performance parameters in either numerical or graphical form.)

